main event: An unidentified flying object was detected on radar near Gray AFB, Killeen, Texas on 30 August 1958.
interesting points: The object was tracked at a speed of 3700 knots and an azimuth of 175 degrees,The observation lasted for 6 minutes with two minutes of radar tracking,The object's behavior was described as conflicting with typical radar targets,The radar speed was later noted as 3302 knots; information was insufficient for proper evaluation,There was no photograph associated with the report.
sighted object: unidentified flying object detected on radar
witness description: S/SGT Honeycutt and another operator watched the radar track
